%N A396366 Decimal expansion of the lambda (scale) constant in the SELU activation function.
%C A396366 SELU(x) = scale*(max(0,x)+min(0,alpha*(exp(x)-1))).
%C A396366 SELU is an activation function derived from ELU (Exponential Linear Unit), which uses the identity function for x >= 0 and exp(x)-1 for x <= 0.
%C A396366 It multiplies the negative-region output of ELU by the constant alpha and additionally scales the entire function by the constant lambda so that the outputs of a neural network converge toward zero mean and unit variance.
%H A396366 Günter Klambauer, Thomas Unterthiner, Andreas Mayr, and Sepp Hochreiter, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1706.02515">Self-Normalizing Neural Networks</a>, arXiv:1706.02515 [cs.LG], 2017.
%F A396366 Equals sqrt(2/(1 + (sqrt(2/Pi)/(1 - exp(1/2)*erfc(1/sqrt(2))))^2*(1 - 2*exp(1/2)*erfc(1/sqrt(2)) + exp(2)*erfc(sqrt(2))))).
%e A396366 1.0507009873554804934193349852946...
%t A396366 RealDigits[Sqrt[2/(1 + (Sqrt[2/Pi] / (1 - Exp[1/2]*Erfc[1/Sqrt[2]]))^2 * (1 - 2*Exp[1/2] * Erfc[1/Sqrt[2]] + Exp[2]*Erfc[Sqrt[2]]))], 10, 105][[1]] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 24 2026 *)
%o A396366 (PARI) lambda = sqrt(2 / (1 + (sqrt(2/Pi) / (1 - exp(1/2)*erfc(1/sqrt(2.))))^2 * (1 - 2*exp(1/2)*erfc(1/sqrt(2.)) + exp(2)*erfc(sqrt(2.)))))
%Y A396366 Cf. A396365.
